query: How to create the data management plan?
response: Create the data management plan using either the Word template at the bottom of this page or with the DPM Tuuli data management planning tool, which both contain instructions. Find the link to DMP Tuuli from the links-list.
documents:
["The data management plan will complement the thesis plan, so avoid unnecessary duplication: include the data management plan as an annex to your thesis plan.
Creating data management plan
Create the data management plan using either the Word template at the bottom of this page or with the DPM Tuuli data management planning tool. They both contain instructions. Find the link to DMP Tuuli from the links-list.", "So proceed in the following order:
Create a thesis plan, attached by a data management plan. If the thesis is a literature review, you don’t need a data management plan.
Apply the research permit, when necessary. Attach the data management plan and a possible research plan.
Begin to collect data.
Store the data appropriately (according to your plan) during the thesis process.
Archive, open or dispose the data (according to your plan) when the thesis is completed.
The data management plan is part of the thesis plan
The purpose of the data management plan is to ensure that the thesis follows good scientific practice. It also aims to ensure that the research material is not compromised at any stage. In the data management plan, you will describe what data you will collect, how you will store and share it, any legal (e.g. data protection) or contractual issues, and what will happen to the data when the thesis is completed."]

query: How to create the data management plan?
response: Use either the Word template provided at the bottom of this page or with DMP Tuuli tool from links-list for creating a data management plan, which is part of your thesis plan. It should detail what type of empirical data you will collect and how to store it securely during research process until completion where appropriate archiving, sharing open access options, disposal as per the plan are carried out respecting legal or contractual issues surrounding handling such sensitive material throughout its life cycle in your thesis project.

query: What does phase 2 of the thesis process include?
response:
Phase 2 of the thesis process includes "Thesis implementation" as mentioned in the document:

**Phase 2 (Two thirds of thesis completed) - Thesis implementation**

Bachelor 6 ECTS credits = 162 working hours. If you do your thesis 15 hours a week, it will take 10-11 weeks.
Master 10 ECTS credits = 270 working hours. If you do your thesis 15 hours a week, it will take 18 weeks.
documents:
["## **Phase 3 (Thesis ready for assessment) - Thesis reporting and assessment ** Bachelor 4 ECTS credits = 108 working hours. If you do your thesis 15 hours a week, it will take 7 weeks. Master 10 ECTS credits = 270 working hours. If you do your thesis 15 hours a week, it will take 18 weeks. **Tasks contained in phase 3 ** Writing the thesis and the first draft of the whole work ready for preliminary examination. Final comments from the principal thesis tutor, the 2nd examiner and the commissioner. The commissioner needs 20 days (approx. three weeks) to get acquainted with your thesis, comment on it and write the commissioner's statement. Allow a total of about six weeks for review and corrections based on comments. **Also remember these final tasks ** • Agree on the thesis presentation with your principal thesis tutor. • Check that the final thesis name in Finnish and English is in the thesis information section in Wihi. • Agree on writing a maturity test with the principal thesis tutor during the preliminary examination. The maturity test must be approved when the thesis is assessed. • Submit the self-assessment and the statement of the commissioner to Wihi. In addition, master's students will also return a maturity test to Wihi. • Return the completed thesis to Wihi in Plagiarism Check field for checking text similarity and for archiving. • Save your thesis in Theseus and copy and save the Theseus link to Wihi. The assessment cannot be completed if the link is not in Wihi. **Last tasks before graduation ** • Get a PDF file of the thesis evaluation statement from Wihi, it will not be sent to you separately. • Check your study attainments in Peppi. • Apply for a certificate through electronic services.


-----

", "# **Thesis process scheduling, how much time do you need at different phases of the ** **thesis? **
## **Previous studies ** Adequate knowledge of your field Studies of Research and Development (Bachelor) or studies of Research-based Development (Master) **Topic ideation ** Discuss the topic of the thesis with a career tutor, for example, or participate in topic brainstorming workshops, etc. **Prepare a topic proposal to Wihi ** https://wihi.jamk.fi You get the principal thesis tutor. **Schedule the thesis process in Wihi ** Bachelor 15 ECTS credits = 405 working hours. If you do your thesis 15 hours a week, it will take 27 weeks = 6-7 months. Master 30 ECTS credits = 810 working hours. If you do your thesis 15 hours a week, it will take 54 weeks = 13-14 months. **Phase 1 (One third of thesis completed) - Thesis plan ** Bachelor 3 ECTS credits = 81 working hours. If you do your thesis 15 hours a week, it will take 5-6 weeks. Master 7 ECTS credits = 189 working hours. If you do your thesis 15 hours a week, it will take 12-13 weeks. Bachelor: Thesis writing 2 cr = 54 working hours. If you do your thesis 15 hours a week, it will take 3-4 weeks. Master: Research Writing 3 cr = 81 working hours. If you do your thesis 15 hours a week, it will take 5-6 weeks. **Phase 2 (Two thirds of thesis completed) - Thesis implementation ** Bachelor 6 ECTS credits = 162 working hours. If you do your thesis 15 hours a week, it will take 10-11 weeks. Master 10 ECTS credits = 270 working hours. If you do your thesis 15 hours a week, it will take 18 weeks.


-----

"]

query: How to name thesis when the work has only one author?
documents:
["See the video below on how to publish your thesis in the Theseus collection.
Oops! This video will not be shown because you have disabled the marketing cookies. To see the video, accept marketing cookies.
File format PDF/A
Publish your thesis in PDF/A format. This is NOT the same file format that you use for Wihi. See the links on how to convert the file.Also, note that the name of the file will appear as such on the public website.
If the work has only one author, the filename is: Lastname_Firstname
If the work has more than one author, the filename is: Lastname_Lastname
NB: This instruction only applies to the file to be saved to Theseus. Naming convention in submitting the work in Wihi is in section Return the thesis (see the links!).
Theseus can only store files up to 75 megabytes in size. Contact the Jamk library if your thesis is larger or if your thesis has e.g. an external recording as a separate attachment.
Copying and saving the Theseus link to Wihi", "Parenthetical citation: (Wilson-Harris, 2020)
Narrative citation: Wilson-Harris (2020)
Further information and examples from APA Style
Book review
Njau, L.S., & Isuja, S.P. (2019). [Review of the book The challenge for Africa, by W. Maathai]. International Journal of Knowledge, Innovation & Entrepreneurship, 7(1), pp. 93–95. Retrieved from https://www.ijkie.org
If the DOI is available, use it. Otherwise, use the URL of the journal’s homepage preceded by Retrieved from.
Parenthetical citation: (Njau & Isuja, 2019)
Narrative citation: Njau and Isuja (2019)
Published dissertation or thesis
Balazs, M. (2020). Internationalization of a health care mobile application: Case study of Onerva Hoivaviestintä Oy. [Master’s thesis, Jamk University of Applied Sciences]. Theseus. http://urn.fi/URN:NBN:fi:amk–2020070519503
Parenthetical citation: (Balazs, 2020)
Narrative citation: Balazs (2020)
Further information and examples from APA Style
Data Sets
Data set"]

query: How to write parenthetical citation in book review?
response:
Parenthetical citation style is used within the text of an essay, paper, or article when referring to a source. It enables readers to find that information easily without interrupting their reading flow by providing immediate and direct access points to your references in parentheses following specific phrases like quotes, paraphrases, or summaries from another work you cite directly within the body of text (Njau & Isuja, 2019; Barbieri & Scherer, 2012). The parenthetical citations should include both authors' last names and publication year for sources with multiple authors. When referencing a book review in an article or essay using this citation style:
(Njau & Isuja, 2019; Wilson-Harris, 2020)
